{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770322060,"nonce":"5Bkb14dfr2sDmKVqThNVmwBAOe4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oqL8X","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/172","origin":"github"},"title":"Add pre-commit hook to detect outdated documentation references","message":"## Problem\n\nDocumentation can become stale when code changes. In PR #171, we:\n1. Removed support for `configs/*.repos` files\n2. But several docs still referenced them\n3. Only caught this during manual verification\n\n## Solution\n\nCreate a pre-commit hook that scans documentation for potentially outdated references.\n\n## Implementation\n\nAdd to `.pre-commit-config.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\n- repo: local\n  hooks:\n    - id: check-doc-references\n      name: Check for outdated documentation references\n      entry: .agent/hooks/check_doc_references.py\n      language: python\n      files: '\\.md$'\n```\n\nScript should flag:\n- References to `configs/*.repos` (should be in project repo)\n- Usage patterns that contradict actual script behavior\n- Dead command examples\n\n## Benefits\n\n- Catches documentation drift early\n- Forces docs to be updated with code changes\n- Prevents PR merge with inconsistent docs","files":null}]}